---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms & Conditions • SwiftLink Logistics"
  description="Read the Terms and Conditions governing the use of SwiftLink Logistics services and website."
  canonicalPath="/terms"
>
  <section class="py-24 bg-slate-950">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tighter mb-2">Terms & Conditions</h1>
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-12">Last updated: April 10, 2026</p>

      <div class="prose-slate space-y-8 text-slate-300 text-[0.95rem] leading-relaxed">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p>By accessing or using the SwiftLink Logistics, LLC ("SwiftLink," "we," "us," or "our") website and services, you agree to be bound by these Terms & Conditions. If you do not agree, do not use our website or services.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">2. Services</h2>
          <p>SwiftLink Logistics is a third-party logistics (3PL) freight brokerage that arranges the transportation of goods between shippers and carriers. We do not own or operate trucks. All transportation is performed by independent, licensed motor carriers. Quotes provided are estimates and may vary based on shipment details, market conditions, and carrier availability.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">3. User Responsibilities</h2>
          <p>You agree to provide accurate and complete information when submitting quote requests, booking shipments, or communicating with our team. You are responsible for ensuring that shipments comply with all applicable federal, state, and local laws, including hazardous materials regulations where applicable.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">4. Quotes & Pricing</h2>
          <p>All quotes are non-binding estimates unless a formal rate confirmation or contract has been executed. Pricing is subject to change based on fuel surcharges, accessorial charges, weight discrepancies, or other factors. Final charges will be reflected on the invoice or bill of lading.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">5. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>SwiftLink Logistics acts solely as a broker and is not liable for loss, damage, or delay of cargo during transit. Carrier liability is governed by the carrier's tariff and applicable law. SwiftLink's total liability for any claim shall not exceed the brokerage fees collected for the specific shipment in question.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">6. Claims</h2>
          <p>Cargo claims must be submitted in writing within nine (9) months of the delivery date. SwiftLink will assist in facilitating claims with the responsible carrier but is not the insurer of the cargo.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">7. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>All content on this website, including text, graphics, logos, and images, is the property of SwiftLink Logistics, LLC and is protected by U.S. copyright and trademark laws. You may not reproduce, distribute, or create derivative works without our prior written consent.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">8. Indemnification</h2>
          <p>You agree to indemnify and hold harmless SwiftLink Logistics, its officers, employees, and agents from any claims, damages, or expenses arising from your use of our services or your violation of these Terms.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">9. Governing Law</h2>
          <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Michigan, without regard to conflict-of-law principles. Any disputes shall be resolved in the state or federal courts located in Oakland County, Michigan.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">10. Changes to Terms</h2>
          <p>We reserve the right to update these Terms at any time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date. Continued use of our services constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">11. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            If you have questions about these Terms, contact us at
            <a href="mailto:info@swiftlinkusa.com" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline">info@swiftlinkusa.com</a>
            or call <a href="tel:+12489876776" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline">(248) 987-6776</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
